  */
  {
   "LogName": "CREATING AN EVENT",
   "Action": "EditData",
   "Target": "Data/Events/{{ModId}}_Map",
   "Entries": {
    /* ENTRIES: https://github.com/Pathoschild/StardewMods/blob/develop/ContentPatcher/docs/author-guide/action-editdata.md#entries

 "An entry is a top-level block of data in the target data (i.e. a key/value pair in a dictionary or a value in a list)."
    "what the heck does that mean?"
    Most of the time when you look into something you'll see that it looks like this:
    "<KEY>": "<SOME NONSENSE>"
    depending on where/what you're using it on, the key has many ways, edd boy
    since we're in the event scripting, i'll give you an example
    */
    "{{ModId}}_Your_Event_ID_Here/SOME PRECONDITION/MAYBE ANOTHER PRECONDITION/OH BUT WAIT A THIRD PRECONDITION/": "MUSIC/VIEWPORT/ACTORS/the_rest_of_your_event_scripting_here"
    //https://stardewvalleywiki.com/Modding:Event_data
   }
  },
  //you're playing with the big bois now *snaps fingers* *spawns a snake*
  {
   "LogName": "A crime to events",
   "Action": "EditData",
   "Target": "Data/Events/AbandonedJojaMart", //MA, THEY'RE MAKING A CRIME ON A VANILLA EVENT!!!
   "TextOperations": [ //textoperations is a <List> https://github.com/Pathoschild/StardewMods/blob/develop/ContentPatcher/docs/author-guide/text-operations.md
    {
     "Operation": "ReplaceDelimited",
     "Target": [ "Entries", "missingBundleComplete" ],
     "Search": "communityCenter",
